column1: Hard Mode unlocked! Access in 'New Game'
Oh, is this how it ends...
Poor aim - and a poor reaper.
I'm not here for YOU, reaper!
Some stages have multiple entrances - try another one.
Try switching to a different weapon.
Try purchasing a different weapon - if you have the souls.
Remember to conserve powerful ammo for stronger enemies.
Knocking can split enemies apart, making it easier.
Make sure to check the mission objective.
Vents can help you flank enemies.
If your current strategy isn't working, try something else.
If you can't make progress, take a break and come back with a fresh perspective.
Remember to keep cool! You'll have a harder time playing if frustrated.

This game contains rapidly flashing lights. If you have a history of seizures or epilepsy, disable 'Flashing Lights' in the options or consult a physician before playing.##This game also contains topics of death and suicide.
6 bullets#49 damage#3 headshot multiplier#Bullets regenerate over time
The zombies are selling some strange drug. Find out what it is.
Let's get the attention of their leader. Burn all their drugs.
A low level dealer, Puff, might know about their supplier. Kill him.
The first address leads to a Hellhound pound. End it.
The second address leads to a house with a missing Candle.
Find the location of Roland's warehouse.
Destroy the warehouse where the Zombie Kingz store their drugs.
Kill Roland, the leader of the Zombie Kingz.
The vampires are running a club - find out why.
The vampires' numbers are worrying - thin it out.
Another club, another safe - maybe this one will have useful information.
What are the vampires doing near the docks?
Twin vampires are running a brothel. Shut it down.
This club is strangely quiet - what happened?
The vampire leader must know about what happened.
The vampires are being turned to ash - stop the next harvest.
She knows about the conversion. Kill her and stop the ash.
The skeletons have been congregating near the docks. Find out why.
They've been attempting to build a new base. Destroy its inhabitants.
Two bars, back to back. Eliminate both.
The Candles have found the shipping location..
Timur is a high ranking Dredged. I'll find out what he knows.
I have to find out where Ibzan, The Dredged leader, lives.
Ibzan's home is heavily guarded, but must contain important information.
I need snipers on the roof - but must get rid of the Vall first.
I have to stop Ibzan and The Dredged from leaving this Place.
Long-range slashing weapon. Can't be thrown.
High damage but loud. Holds 5 bullets.
Silent weapon, but lower damage. Holds 10 bullets.
Very high damage on headshots. Holds 7 rounds.
Quick melee weapon. Can be thrown.
Silent weapon with laser. Holds 30 rounds.
Beat the entire game within 1 hour without quitting.
Beat the entire game without dying or quitting.
Get a five star rating on every mission.
Clear a stage with only headshot kills.
Kill an undead... using the toilet.
Clear a stage with only melee weapons.
Kill Puff without using the Tommy Gun.
Clear 'The Bloody Mary' without letting any vampires revive.
Kill Amber with a melee weapon, and Evelyn with a ranged weapon.
Destroy a body as it's being revived.
Clear 'Timur The Tinkerer' with only trap kills.
Clear Vall's nest using only headshots.
Testing. And then testing some more.       Big space.
Testing sounds and vooooooooooooooowels. Bimp. Bimp. Banp. Bimp.
Zombie 1 test. I am testing meeee
Zombie 2 test. I am testing meeee
Zombie 3 test. I am testing meeee
You shouldn't have listened to that.
It doesn't look well. The candle is clutching a note.
"COLD. WHERE ARE YOU. GO 1023 8th NE Highway Ave"
You need more men protecting the ash!
We've got guns on every floor, reaper. Go home.
We know you're here, reaper. Go home.
A reaper? Zombies and their drugs...
A reaper? Ha! And the bogeyman too?
The... grim reaper? Are you joking?
I don't usually do this but...
PROTECT THE ASH. IT'S WORTH MORE THAN YOU.
You have done a good job, friend. Feel pride in what you help craft.
A shipping manifest is taped inside
I should tell the boss. Maybe his Candles know something.
MORE TIME... I JUST NEED MORE TIME.
There is an information sheet taped to the side of the car - with an address.
Just one more day... and then we get paid.
Finally. Gotta get back before boss sees we're missing.
I want to see you in the light...!
Aww, shy? Step into the light!
Don't be scared... step into the light!
W-woah! I've never been this close to a reaper before!
We are so close. We will be warm soon.
Come - do not fear my true form.
Let me see you, friend. I just want to talk.
I know where you are friend. I'll find you.
No - you have worked so hard. I think it is time for a rest.
Press 'Q' over an enemy or light, and we'll take it out!
...candles doing reaper work...this would've never happened before...
"&b&Twins&!& lost at sea - #of lust and of pain. #Women without love, #cannot live with me."
Magical charms - the vampires prefer bottles. They will glow noticeably blue.
While the Candles couldn't see inside the cargo, they did spot a crane with a weapon on top.
The flames stay extinguished - but a voice still speaks.
The Stela's are a royal family of vampires. Any activity in the 1000 Year Royals would not go without them knowing.
The flames roar to life - and I see visions inside.
The twins have somehow made each other their phylactery. I will have to kill both at nearly the same time.
"Skeletons are found, #no flesh and no love.#Stop their harvest -#or &y&Ibzan&!& is crowned.
Large zombies with shotguns. Takes a few shots to the head to bring them down.
Those who take their own life come back as skeletons, destined forever to roam this Place.
To get a clear shot at Vall I will have to get on the roof of a nearby building... while avoiding her sniper fire.
By the time I arrived, the harvest will be near complete. I'll only have a minute to destroy all the harvest totems.
The vampires are both the most attractive and sexually active undead, so it comes naturally.
The Candles have found the location of all the skeletons' shipping containers - but many skeletons guard the location. Kill the Generals first, or draw them to a trap by killing nearby skeletons.
Rolands' house is filled with many guards - but the only target is Roland. I'll separate him from his men.
"He cannot be free.#I cannot forgive.#A man - undead#cannot live with me."
The "meat portal" Timur constructed must be destroyed - or the skeletons, and all the undead with them, could leave this Place.
"Around Ibzan - coils,#undead forgotten.#Open their coffins, #uncover their spoils."

Candles have spotted vampires coming and going from the industrial district - the same address I found in the safe. I'll find out what they're doing. ##Suddenly, the flames speak: "The goals of undead are always the same."
"No moment to flee -# he should not be here.#&y&A man with a heart&!&,#cannot live with me."
Demons bring high-powered weaponry from their lands. I will have to be careful and use cover accordingly.
Some vampires have their souls outside of their body, stored in &y&phylacteries&!&. They must be destroyed to kill the vampire.
The fireplace began to speak, #"Flesh caskets breathe.#Burn the ash,#scatter their teeth."
"No forest - a lone tree.#Kills her own for escape.#A woman without guilt,#cannot live with me."
"&y&Generals&!&, unchained!# Corpses to surface. #Find those who have drowned,#and drown them again."
"Hellhounds from beneath, #bred by the undead.#Go stop the weeping, #and gnashing of teeth."
The flames roar to life - and I see blood inside.
There's a &y&bouncer&!& on the far side of the house. I can kill him to get his weapon.
The flames roar to life - and a voice speaks out. "Another life, well returned!"

The undead have somehow been turning their own bodies into ash... is that the purpose of all these clubs? &y&Sir&!& &y&Stela&!&, the head of the 1000 Year Royals, most likely knows how this was done.##"He will know the key,#betrayal of kin.#A man without guilt,#cannot live with me."
"They climb to the sky,#scouting for reapers.#Do not let them build - #they will fly too high."
I see visions of Charon, the Ferryman. He may be interested in the souls I have collected for our mutual employer - I should see him at the &y&docks&!& before my next mission.
The zombies have hung up security cameras. They don't do much, but will scream if it sees me for too long. I'll avoid them, or shoot them down.
A club the Candles have been investigating has suddenly gone quiet - along with the Candles. What happened inside?
"Their location - explained!#Burn the ash, #burn the dead,#and free souls contained."

"&y&Demons&!& - they cross the river!##Ibzan feels the flame-#Hire help from beyond.#Demons are not dead#but die just the same." ##Ibzan is getting his car serviced at a nearby garage, defended by Demons. The return address to his home should be on the car.
"More, more, so many more. #So many corpses, #who forgot to die."
Undead are easiest to kill when alone.
Shotgun weapons are strongest near doors and entryways, where enemies can't react until it's too late.
Hellhounds are three headed dogs with amazing sense of hearing, but they can't open doors. I'll use that to my advantage.
The Candles tell me that Puff keeps an old machine gun in his basement - something he stole from the Trideads. I am sure it still works.
"A man of light," spoke the fireplace, "should not have to spend his time in darkness."
"Attempting to lead,#his creed to salvation.#&y&A man with ambition&!&,#cannot live with me."
Charon lives at the docks - I can exchange souls for weapons before I accept my mission.
The Candles have reported Madam Stela has multiple phylacteries - I will have to destroy them all before taking Madam Stela down.
Dancing vampires won't notice your presence - unless you shoot them.
Shadows cast along the wall, and the flames show me silhouettes of Puff's death.##This is the first time my employer has given me a specific target - and I succumb to the thrill.
My mission is to destroy all the ash - but it is best if I focus on killing the undead first.
His death will shatter the Zombie Kingz leadership - I must remember that the mission is to kill Roland, not the others.
"She paints with such glee!#A splattered canvas.#A woman of vision#cannot live with me."
I have found the location of the meat portal, but it is heavily defended by snipers. The &y&Candles&!& have offered their assistance, but I must first kill &y&Vall&!& - the best of the demon snipers.
"Look upon your reflection," said the fireplace, "and remember that you are different. You are not undead."
The flames roar to life - and you see visions of a man, Puff.
"His home is exposed.#Find the portal.#Prove him mortal.#Leave him decomposed." ##Ibzan's apartment must contain data about the &y&portal&!& The Dredged are planning to construct.
There is no reply, but the flames continues to crackle.
"Pale moonlight. #Touch -  no heat. #&b&Vampires&!& flock, #find out why."
The flames continue to crackle - it no longer has missions for me.
Creatures from beyond Charon's river, they sometimes make their way up as hired mercenaries. The Candles nor my employer know how the skeletons are paying for their service.
There is no intel. The fireplace remains quiet.
"The undead begin to crop#strange &b&powders&!& from below.#Incite the flame -#eject their brains!#And see what it contains."
"&y&Timur&!& is free.#Knows purpose of flesh.#A man with desire,#cannot live with me."
A new drug called "ash." His candles say that it makes you feel like you're alive again. The flames - my employer - want to know more.
"The vampires reform - #a lounge not too far. #Discover their aim, #and bring them a storm."##This lounge contains a safe - maybe I can understand why these clubs have been suddenly appearing.
The Candles will support from above - but they have limited ammunition. I will have to make sure I use their help conservatively.
Tall undead, said to be formed by betrayal from a lover. They are much more dangerous than zombies - I'll have to make sure that every shot counts.
"My Candles tell me tales,#&y&Undead&!& form and blossom#Find their abode and knock,#And free them from their jails." ##The flames never spoke in prose.
"His heart long gone, #Ibzan leads The Dredged.#You must bring his end - #he cannot do it alone."
Commonly known as lich, Generals have the ability to bring damaged skeletons back to life. The source of this power is unknown, even to the Candles.
Amber and Evelynn run &y&brothels&!& downtown. They are high ranking members of the 1000 Year Royals - they must understand the crytpic messages I've been finding in the club safes.
I see two entrances to the house. The left entrance has less zombies, but the right entrance has more weapons. My choice.
"Timur is the chief engineer for The Dredged. His crafting skills are only matched by his paranoia - his lab is outfitted with traps. I will have to tread carefully.
"I... thought you could use companionship," spoke the fireplace. "Life is not meant to be spent alone."
"My &y&Candle&!& has searched,#but never returned." ##The second address is familiar to the fireplace - I'll find what happened to the Candle.
The Candles never engage in combat - but our employer has made an exception.
Some vampires will have phylacteries in difficult places, and will have to be killed multiple times.
The Zombie Kingz have become scared of my hunt. They have begun heavily guarding a nearby motel - I will find what they are hiding.
"Candles do not know,#the &y&skeletons'&!& aim. #Go and peer inside, #their precious cargo."
Technicians plant mines when spooked - but the mines can be used against them.
The fire licks and sneers. Undead, zombies included, must be helped towards the afterlife.
Sir Stela's private condominum is heavily guarded, so expect heavy opposition.
To help fight the Demon arsenal, Charon has lent us an extremely powerful weapon. I can find it in my car - I'll use it liberally.
Candles are the eyes and ears of the flames, always observing and bringing information.
The flames roar to life, with more vigor than usual. My employer is happy with success.
The Candles tell me that Zombie Kingz patrols are nearby. I'll have to be quick, in case there are reinforcements.
